    <thetext>Description of problem:

Applications that are linked with the current packaged version will crash with Wayland. Issues have been fixed upstream^[1] however the package has not been version bumped in a long time.

[1] https://github.com/glfw/glfw/commit/704dc3e34d024faf36fd6d4112796686c3fa2804

Version-Release number of selected component (if applicable):

$ rpm -q glfw
glfw-3.1.1-3.fc24.x86_64

How reproducible:

Take any glfw linked GL application and try to run it with Wayland.

Actual results:

Seg fault

Expected results:

My application to work naturally.

Additional info:

Bumping the package version should be all that is required to resolve this issue.

Kind Regards,
Edward.</thetext>
